NEUTRON FISSION OF U-235 AND U-233 -.
.A MIXTURE OF 106 MG URANIUM DIOXIDE, ENRICHED TO
93 PERCENT U-235 AND 5 CM*3 OF BARIUM STEARATE POWDER.
.FOR U-233, 50 MG OF URANIUM DIOXIDE, ENRICHED TO 99.3

x4codes.hlp: Off-line mass separation of a product

x4freetext: ON LINE MASS SEPERATION OF PRODUCTS.
CUMMULATIVE YIELDS ARE DETERMINED FROM THE
ACTIVITY OF RARE GASES WITH RESPECT TO A REFERENCE
SEPERATED MASSES ARE IMPLANTED ONTO AN ALUMINIUM
FOIL AND TRANSFERED TO A SYSTEM OF TWO THIN PLASTIC
.MEASUREMENT OF RARE GAS ACTIVITY DURING IRRADIATION
IS PROPORTIONAL TO THE CUMMULATIVE YIELD OF THE
.MEASURMENT OF THE ACTIVITY AFTER THE END OF THE
IRRADIATION PERIOD IS DUE ONLY TO DECAY OF NON-GASEOUS
PRECURSORS IMPLANTED IN THE ALUMINIUM FOIL.
PLASTIC SCINTILLATORS, 1 MM THICK, SOLID ANGLE
CORRESPONDING CUMMULATIVE YIELDS. AS MANY OF THESE ARE
CLOSE TO THE MASS CHAIN YIELDS, ESTABLISHED DATA FROM
MEEK AND RIDER, NEDO-12154-1,1974, FOR CHAIN YIELDS
AND FRACTIONAL CUMMULATIVE YIELDS ARE USED.
.QUOTED ERRORS REFLECT SIMPLY THE SCATTER OF SEVERAL
